Module c195.c195assessment
Package c195.c195assessment.model

Class Appointment

java.lang.Object
c195.c195assessment.model.Appointment
public class Appointment extends Object
Represents an appointment, including details such as title, type, start and end times, and associated customer and user IDs. This class mirrors a record in the "Appointments" table of the database.

    • Appointment

      public Appointment()
      Constructs an empty Appointment object with default values.

    • Appointment

      public Appointment(String title, String description, String location, String type, LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end, String createdBy, String lastUpdatedBy, int customerID, int userID, int contactID)
      Constructs a partially filled Appointment object, primarily used when creating a new appointment before creating the entry in the database. The appointmentID, createDate, and lastUpdate are then generated by the database.
      Parameters:
      title - The appointment's title.
      description - The appointment's description.
      location - The appointment's location.
      type - The type of appointment.
      start - The start time and date of the appointment.
      end - The end time and date of the appointment.
      createdBy - The username of the user who created the appointment.
      lastUpdatedBy - The username of the user who last updated the appointment.
      customerID - The ID of the customer associated with the appointment.
      userID - The ID of the user associated with the appointment.
      contactID - The ID of the contact associated with the appointment.

    • Appointment

      public Appointment(int appointmentID, String title, String description, String location, String type, LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end, LocalDateTime createDate, String createdBy, Instant lastUpdate, String lastUpdatedBy, int customerID, int userID, int contactID)
      Constructs an Appointment object with all fields specified. This constructor is typically used when retrieving an existing appointment from the database.
      Parameters:
      appointmentID - The primary key ID of the appointment.
      title - The appointment's title.
      description - The appointment's description.
      location - The appointment's location.
      type - The type of appointment.
      start - The start time and date of the appointment.
      end - The end time and date of the appointment.
      createDate - The date and time the appointment was created.
      createdBy - The username of the user who created the appointment.
      lastUpdate - The last time and date the appointment was updated.
      lastUpdatedBy - The username of the user who last updated the appointment.
      customerID - The ID of the customer associated with the appointment.
      userID - The ID of the user associated with the appointment.
      contactID - The ID of the contact associated with the appointment.
